Pile on the veggies

Subway lets you add as many veggies as you want at no additional charge! This is a great way to add more nutrients to your sandwich.

Go light on the spreads

Choose light mayo or skip mayo all together and save 50-100 calories. Add some zest with mustard or honey mustard instead.

Choose sweets carefully

Choose apples or a yogurt parfait instead of cookies if you're looking for a sweet ending to your meal.

name: Little Caesars Pizza
guide:
Thin is In

Ditch the deep dish and go for the thinner regular or pretzel crust instead - you'll save up to 100 calories.

Veg Out

Pass on the pepperoni and load up your pizza with veggies for an added crunch and nutritional boost!

Skip the Dip

Just 1 container of Caesar's dipping sauces can set you back up to 380 calories. If you want to add a little kick to your slice, add calorie-free red pepper flakes or oregano.

name: Panda Express
guide:
Better bowl

Pick a perfectly portioned Panda Bowl and pair 1 entree with 1 side. Skip the Entree Plates which come with 2 or 3 entrees plus a side.

Wok smart

Look for items marked Wok Smart on the menu and you are guaranteed an entree with 300 calories or less. The lowest of the low? The 150-calorie Broccoli Beef or the 170-calorie Mushroom Chicken

Slim side

Skip the 400 calorie Steamed Rice and the 500 calorie Fried Rice or Chow Mein. Go for the fresh Mixed Vegetables for only 80 calories.

name: Jimmy John's
guide:
Slim Subs

Skip the high calorie Giant Club Sandwiches and go for a Plain Slim instead. Your best bets are the Slim Roast Beef and Slim Turkey Breast which clock in with less than 500 calories each. Ask them to add lettuce and tomato to add an (almost) calorie free crunch. Plain Slims too plain? Try the Big John or Turkey Tom subs for only about 50-100 calories more.

The Unwich

Cut even more calories (and carbs!) by ordering your sub as an Unwich. They'll swap the bread for a lettuce wrap, saving you 280 calories.

Smart Side

Gotta have chips with that sandwich? A bag of Thinny Jimmy Chips will only add 130 calories to your meal.

name: IHOP
guide:
Simple & fit

To keep calories in check, order one of the items marked Simple & Fit, like the Simple & Fit Vegetable Omelette or Simple & Fit 2-Egg Breakfast. Each clocks in with less than 400 calories.

Proper pancakes

If it’s gotta be pancakes, keep a lid on sugar and white flour with a short stack (3 pancakes) of the Original Buttermilk Pancakes. Go easy on the syrup - just 2 tablespoons of the Maple Old Fashioned Syrup packs 110 calories. Better yet, try topping your pancakes with the Cinnamon Apple Compote (45 calories) or Sugar Free Syrup (15 calories) instead. 

Lighter lunch and dinner

Not there for breakfast? Try the Citrus Chicken Pecan Salad. It’s 670 calories’ worth of greens, grilled chicken, orange slices, and pecans.

name: Chili's
guide:
Lighter Entrees

Keep your entree around 500 calories by ordering a “Lighter Choice” menu item. 

Slim Sides

Cut calories and boost veggies by substituting a side of broccoli or asparagus for fries, mashed potatoes, onion rings, or cornbread.

Get Creative

You can create your own low-calorie taco or enchilada platter with the Fresh Mex Pairing menu. Pair any one taco or enchilada with a House Salad and the standard sides of rice and beans for a 600 calorie Fresh Mex meal.

name: Chick-fil-A
guide:
Go grilled

To keep calories and fat in check, stick with grilled chicken. The Grilled Market Salad, Grilled Chicken Cool Wrap, Grilled Chicken Sandwich, and Grilled Nuggets all clock in with less than 350 calories.

Add fruits and vegetables

Pair your chicken with a Side Salad or Fruit Cup instead of Waffle Fries, Coleslaw, or soup. You'll save calories and get a healthy dose of fruits or veggies.

Be breakfast savvy

Skip the fatty fried chicken, bacon or sausage bagels, biscuits, and burritos and order a Greek Yogurt Parfait or Multigrain Oatmeal instead.

guide:
Go Naked

Skip the deep-fried Traditional Wings, Boneless Wings, and Chicken Tenders. Try the grilled Naked Tenders instead - 4 pieces clock in with only 170 calories.

Splurge on Salad

Load up on veggies and keep calories in check with a Garden Chicken Salad topped with grilled or blackened chicken. 

Smart Sides

Skip the high-calorie fries, onion rings, and chips and pair a Side Salad or carrot and celery Veggie Boat with your Naked Tenders.

name: Golden Corral
guide:
Better Buffet

To avoid overeating at a buffet, stick to just one plate of food. Browse through the buffet and decide what you are going to eat before grabbing a plate so you won’t be tempted to take every item that you see.

Very Veggie

Keep calories in check by filling half your plate with non-starchy veggies like broccoli, cauliflower, green beans, cabbage, or asparagus. Choose steamed vegetables over those in a buttery or creamy sauce or casserole.

Proper Portions

Devote one quarter of your plate to a lean protein such as baked, broiled, grilled or sauteed chicken or fish. FIll the remaining quarter of your plate with a starch or grain. Look for baked sweet potatoes, beans, corn, or whole grains like brown rice.

name: Panera Bread
guide:
Better Breakfast

Skip the muffins, scones, and pastries and grab a hearty bowl of Steel Cut Oatmeal. Not an oatmeal fan? Try the Strawberry Granola Parfait, Seasonal Fruit Cup, or any of the three Breakfast Power Sandwiches.

Think Thin

Trim the calories from your bagel and schmear with a thin Sprouted Grain Bagel Flat topped with a reduced-fat cream cheese spread. 

Veg Out

With over a dozen salads on the menu, it’s easy to get your veggies at Panera. Most full-size salads clock in with only around 500 calories, so munch on! If it’s gotta be a sandwich, try pairing just half a sandwich with a salad as a You Pick 2 combo.

name: Arby's
guide:
Stick with the Classics

Order what Arby’s is known for: roast beef. The Roast Beef Classic sandwich clocks in with only 360 calories. Pair your sandwich with a Chopped Side Salad.

Beyond the Beef

Not a roast beef fan? Try the Chopped Farmhouse Salad with Roast Turkey or Jr. Ham & Cheddar Melt to keep a lid on calories. Skip the turkey sandwiches and wraps, which can hit 800 calories.

Slimmer sides

Go grilled

Switch out some or all of your fried chicken order for grilled chicken to decrease fat and calories.

Drink smart

If you’re drinking a sugary beverage like soda, order a small to save calories.

name: Starbucks
guide:
Caffeine is a morning necessity for millions worldwide. If you’re not a fan of drinking your coffee black or espresso straight, try these suggestions to skim calories, fat, and sugar from your beverage of choice.

Make your latte “skinny”

Lose the whip and substitute nonfat milk  in your latte to cut fat and calories. Lose the sugary syrups and pump up the flavor with the sugar-free versions instead. 

Downsize

If you can't resist that Caramel Macchiato or Vanilla Latte, stick to a modest Tall or Short size to indulge for fewer calories.

Snack smart

For a healthy breakfast on-the-go, try the Whole-Grain Oatmeal, Reduced-Fat Turkey Bacon Breakfast Sandwich, or the Spinach & Feta Breakfast Wrap. Looking for a snack? Satisfy your sweet tooth with seasonal fruit or a Greek yogurt parfait.  If you need something a bit more substantial to battle the afternoon hunger, try the Protein Bistro Box.

name: Five Guys
guide:
Little Burgers

Going with a little burger (1 patty instead of 2) shaves around 200 calories off of your meal!


Add Veggies

Add vegetable toppings like grilled onions, grilled mushrooms, and tomatoes to your burger instead of bacon and cheese. You will be adding a ton of flavor and nutrition but not the fat.


Go Bunless

Ask for you burger to be wrapped in lettuce instead of a bun. This is a great way to swap the processed carbohydrates and calories in exchange for more vitamins and minerals.

Cut calories and boost veggies by substituting a side of broccoli or asparagus for fries, mashed potatoes, onion rings, or cornbread.

Get Creative

You can create your own low-calorie taco or enchilada platter with the Fresh Mex Pairing menu. Pair any one taco or enchilada with a House Salad and the standard sides of rice and beans for a 600 calorie Fresh Mex meal.

name: Olive Garden
guide:
Go Easy on the Breadsticks

The breadsticks may be tempting, but at 140 calories a pop they can add up quick. Can’t resist? Ask your server not to bring any to your table. 

Think Green

Boost veggies by starting your meal with a House Salad instead of soup. 

Lighter Italian Fare

Most dinner size entrees and pastas have around 1,000 calories. You can cut calories in half by ordering an entree off the Lighter Italian Fare menu. 

Downsize Dessert

If you can’t leave without dessert, try one of the 200 to 300 calorie Dolcini (mini desserts).

name: PF Chang's
guide:
Delightful Dishes
With a long menu full of hidden calorie bombs (1,200-calorie Coconut Curry Vegetables anyone?) it can be challenging to pick a low calorie meal at PF Chang's. Avoid the calorie confusion and order from the Delightful Dishes menu instead. You're guaranteed an entree that has only 600 calories or less. 

Slim Sushi
With only 400 calories or less per roll, sushi is a great low-cal entree choice. Pair a roll with a side of veggies for an extra produce punch.

Dim Sum
If dim sum is what you're after, try the Steamed Pork or Shrimp Dumplings (50 calories per dumpling) or the Vegetable Spring Rolls (around 110 calories per roll).

name: Dairy Queen
guide:
Food items

Dairy Queen offers many items that let you trim the calories but not the flavor. Make a healthy meal by choosing the grilled chicken sandwich and pairing it with a side salad with vinaigrette dressing.  You also can't go wrong with the grilled chicken salad which has a satiating 26 grams of protein and only 160 calories. 

Treats

Dairy Queen has many treat options that can fit into a healthy diet. The trick is to keep serving sizes small and limit extra toppings. Choose the small vanilla cone or the small strawberry sundae for only 240 calories each. The fudge bar is also a great option because it has only 50 calories, is fat free and has no added sugar. If the classic DQ Blizzard is more your style, stick with the mini size to limit the impact on your waistline but still make your tastebuds happy.

name: Starbucks
guide:
Caffeine is a morning necessity for millions worldwide. If you’re not a fan of drinking your coffee black or espresso straight, try these suggestions to skim calories, fat, and sugar from your beverage of choice.

Make your latte “skinny”

Lose the whip and substitute nonfat milk  in your latte to cut fat and calories. Lose the sugary syrups and pump up the flavor with the sugar-free versions instead. 

Downsize

If you can't resist that Caramel Macchiato or Vanilla Latte, stick to a modest Tall or Short size to indulge for fewer calories.

Snack smart

For a healthy breakfast on-the-go, try the Whole-Grain Oatmeal, Reduced-Fat Turkey Bacon Breakfast Sandwich, or the Spinach & Feta Breakfast Wrap. Looking for a snack? Satisfy your sweet tooth with seasonal fruit or a Greek yogurt parfait.  If you need something a bit more substantial to battle the afternoon hunger, try the Protein Bistro Box.

name: Wendy's
guide:
Stick with Jr. size

Getting a burger? Stick with a fewer-than-400-calories Jr. size.  If it's a Frosty you're fantasizing about,  a Jr. size will cost you about 200 calories. That ain't bad.

Choose grilled chicken

For salads, sandwiches, and wraps, choose lean grilled chicken over fried. 

Make a meal out of sides

Pair an order of Rich & Meaty Chili or Baked Potato (hold the cheese) with a Garden Side Salad for a filling meal with around 500 calories.

name: Chipotle
guide:
Toss the tortilla

Skip the 320-calorie flour tortilla in that Burrito and opt for a Burrito Bowl instead. You'll save another 200 calories if you lose the rice and swap the Bowl for a Salad. Or strike a balance: ask for a  Bowl with half lettuce and half rice.

Steak is supreme

It may come as a surprise, but the 150-calorie Steak has fewer calories and less saturated fat than any other meat option at Chipotle. Second best? The 180-calorie Chicken. Or skip the meat altogether and go for the 150-calorie tofu Sofritas instead (but be aware: you'll get 1/3 the protein of the meat options). 

Toppings

If you're getting rice, make it brown. Load up on fiber-rich fajita vegetables, beans, and fresh tomato salsa. Go easy on the higher calorie toppings like cheese, sour cream, and guacamole, which add 100-230 calories a pop.

address: 10515 N MO PAC EXPY STE A125

name: Jack in the Box
guide:
Think Green

Cut calories and boost veggies by ordering a salad topped with grilled chicken. Choose from the classic Grilled Chicken Salad, Chicken Club Salad, or Southwest Chicken Salad. Use only half the dressing to keep calories at 500 or less.

Keep it Small

Skip the big burgers like the Buttery Jack and Jumbo Jack and try the 320-calorie Jr. Jack instead. Pair it with a Side Salad to punch up the produce.

Something Different

Branch out beyond the typical burger or chicken sandwich and try the Chicken Fajita Pita. With only 340 calories, it’s a bargain!

Better Breakfast

If you’re looking for a lighter breakfast, try the 140-calorie Mini Pancakes (260 calories with syrup) or the 280-calorie Breakfast Jack. Hold the Hash Browns and pair your breakfast with the Apple Bites with Caramel Dip instead.

name: McDonald's
guide:
Choose Chicken

Lean, grilled chicken is the way to go at McDonald’s. Try it on a veggie-packed salad with a side of low fat dressing or opt for a grilled chicken sandwich or McWrap (hold the sauce) and pump up the produce with a side of Apple Slices or salad.

Stick with Smaller

If it’s gotta be a burger, stick with a slim 250-calorie Hamburger or 300-calorie Cheeseburger.  Try getting one as part of a Happy Meal (yes, adults can eat these too!). With about 500 calories per meal, you’ll treat your inner child without growing your waistline.   

Breakfast

Start your day with an Egg White Delight McMuffin, Fruit ‘N Yogurt Parfait, or Fruit & Maple Oatmeal. Each clocks in with less than 300 calories. Skip the Hash Browns and get a side of Apple Slices instead.

name: Subway
guide:
Subway is a great place for a protein rich meal on the go. If you follow some of these tips you will satisfy your sandwich craving with a big nutritional punch!

Pile on the veggies

Subway lets you add as many veggies as you want at no additional charge! This is a great way to add more nutrients to your sandwich.

Go light on the spreads

Choose light mayo or skip mayo all together and save 50-100 calories. Add some zest with mustard or honey mustard instead.

Choose sweets carefully

Choose apples or a yogurt parfait instead of cookies if you're looking for a sweet ending to your meal.

name: Taco Bell
guide:
Taco Bell allows for customization on most of their menu items so try these suggestions to make your next taco tastier and healthier.

Fresco Menu

Taco Bell offers 7 signature Fresco items that are big on flavor and are only 350 calories (or less!) and under 10 grams of fat. You can also order most items Fresco Style which can reduce the fat in your meal by up to 25%.

More Veggies

Add tomatoes, onions, peppers, lettuce, or salsa to your meal to boost veggie content. Taco Bell also has a wide selection of vegetarian selections to try.

Up the flavor without the calories

Instead of sour cream, cheese, or a creamy sauce, pour on one or more packets of Border Sauce to up the flavor without the guilt. Each packet is 0 calories and there are 4 varieties to try!

Choose Small Drinks

Keep sugary drinks, like soda, small. Save the larger cups for water or unsweetened tea.

name: Panda Express
guide:
Better bowl

Pick a perfectly portioned Panda Bowl and pair 1 entree with 1 side. Skip the Entree Plates which come with 2 or 3 entrees plus a side.

Wok smart

Look for items marked Wok Smart on the menu and you are guaranteed an entree with 300 calories or less. The lowest of the low? The 150-calorie Broccoli Beef or the 170-calorie Mushroom Chicken

Slim side

Skip the 400 calorie Steamed Rice and the 500 calorie Fried Rice or Chow Mein. Go for the fresh Mixed Vegetables for only 80 calories.

name: Sonic
guide:
Think small

When it comes to burgers, smaller is better. At Sonic, that means a Jr. Burger or Jr. Deluxe Cheeseburger. Got a hankering for a hot dog? Skip the footlong and stick with a regular New York, All-American, or Chicago Dog.

Go wacky

Keep a lid on calories by ordering a Wacky Pack kid's meal. Pair Chicken Strips, a Jr. Burger, Corn Dog, or Hot Dog with Apple Slices and 1% Milk, Orange Juice, or Apple Juice for a 500-calorie meal. 

Trim chicken

With around 450 calories each, the Classic Grilled Chicken Sandwich and Grilled Chicken Wrap are great choices.

name: Burger King
guide:
A smaller sandwich

Want that Whopper? Try a Whopper Jr. for about half the calories. It's a 300-calorie burger bargain.

Beyond the beef

There's plenty of lean poultry on the menu at Burger King. Try it in the Chicken, Apple & Cranberry Salad or on the Tendergrill Chicken Sandwich. Another option? Ditch the meat altogether and try the Veggie Burger instead. 

Swap Sides

Instead of French Fries or Onion Rings, pair your burger or sandwich with a Garden Side Salad or Apple Slices.

name: Jimmy John's
guide:
Slim Subs

Skip the high calorie Giant Club Sandwiches and go for a Plain Slim instead. Your best bets are the Slim Roast Beef and Slim Turkey Breast which clock in with less than 500 calories each. Ask them to add lettuce and tomato to add an (almost) calorie free crunch. Plain Slims too plain? Try the Big John or Turkey Tom subs for only about 50-100 calories more.

The Unwich

Cut even more calories (and carbs!) by ordering your sub as an Unwich. They'll swap the bread for a lettuce wrap, saving you 280 calories.

Smart Side

Gotta have chips with that sandwich? A bag of Thinny Jimmy Chips will only add 130 calories to your meal.

name: Chick-fil-A
guide:
Go grilled

To keep calories and fat in check, stick with grilled chicken. The Grilled Market Salad, Grilled Chicken Cool Wrap, Grilled Chicken Sandwich, and Grilled Nuggets all clock in with less than 350 calories.

Add fruits and vegetables

Pair your chicken with a Side Salad or Fruit Cup instead of Waffle Fries, Coleslaw, or soup. You'll save calories and get a healthy dose of fruits or veggies.

Be breakfast savvy

Skip the fatty fried chicken, bacon or sausage bagels, biscuits, and burritos and order a Greek Yogurt Parfait or Multigrain Oatmeal instead.

guide:
Stick with the Classics

Order what Arby’s is known for: roast beef. The Roast Beef Classic sandwich clocks in with only 360 calories. Pair your sandwich with a Chopped Side Salad.

Beyond the Beef

Not a roast beef fan? Try the Chopped Farmhouse Salad with Roast Turkey or Jr. Ham & Cheddar Melt to keep a lid on calories. Skip the turkey sandwiches and wraps, which can hit 800 calories.

guide:

Stay thin

A thinner crust means fewer calories per slice.


Light Cheese

Order your next pizza with light cheese - less calories but all the flavor!

Keep it thin

Thin crust, that is! Choose a thin crust instead of hand tossed or pan and save up to calories per medium slice.

name: Subway
guide:
Subway is a great place for a protein rich meal on the go. If you follow some of these tips you will satisfy your sandwich craving with a big nutritional punch!

Pile on the veggies

Subway lets you add as many veggies as you want at no additional charge! This is a great way to add more nutrients to your sandwich.

Go light on the spreads

Choose light mayo or skip mayo all together and save 50-100 calories. Add some zest with mustard or honey mustard instead.

Choose sweets carefully

Choose apples or a yogurt parfait instead of cookies if you're looking for a sweet ending to your meal.

name: Dairy Queen
guide:
Food items

Dairy Queen offers many items that let you trim the calories but not the flavor. Make a healthy meal by choosing the grilled chicken sandwich and pairing it with a side salad with vinaigrette dressing.  You also can't go wrong with the grilled chicken salad which has a satiating 26 grams of protein and only 160 calories. 

Treats

Dairy Queen has many treat options that can fit into a healthy diet. The trick is to keep serving sizes small and limit extra toppings. Choose the small vanilla cone or the small strawberry sundae for only 240 calories each. The fudge bar is also a great option because it has only 50 calories, is fat free and has no added sugar. If the classic DQ Blizzard is more your style, stick with the mini size to limit the impact on your waistline but still make your tastebuds happy.

guide:

Make your latte “skinny”

Lose the whip and substitute nonfat milk  in your latte to cut fat and calories. Lose the sugary syrups and pump up the flavor with the sugar-free versions instead. 

Downsize

Snack smart

name: Wingstop
address: Plaza 183 Shopping Center, 13450 Research Boulevard #238, Austin

name: Burger King
guide:
A smaller sandwich

Want that Whopper? Try a Whopper Jr. for about half the calories. It's a 300-calorie burger bargain.

Beyond the beef

There's plenty of lean poultry on the menu at Burger King. Try it in the Chicken, Apple & Cranberry Salad or on the Tendergrill Chicken Sandwich. Another option? Ditch the meat altogether and try the Veggie Burger instead. 

Swap Sides

Instead of French Fries or Onion Rings, pair your burger or sandwich with a Garden Side Salad or Apple Slices.

guide:
Go for the salad

Get a taste of the chicken you love, with a generous helping of greens.

Slimmer sides

Choose corn on the cob or green beans instead of mashed potatoes and gravy to boost your veggie intake and decrease the calorie content of your meal.

Go grilled

Switch out some or all of your fried chicken order for grilled chicken to decrease fat and calories.

Drink smart

If you’re drinking a sugary beverage like soda, order a small to save calories.

name: McDonald's
guide:
Choose Chicken

Lean, grilled chicken is the way to go at McDonald’s. Try it on a veggie-packed salad with a side of low fat dressing or opt for a grilled chicken sandwich or McWrap (hold the sauce) and pump up the produce with a side of Apple Slices or salad.

Stick with Smaller

If it’s gotta be a burger, stick with a slim 250-calorie Hamburger or 300-calorie Cheeseburger.  Try getting one as part of a Happy Meal (yes, adults can eat these too!). With about 500 calories per meal, you’ll treat your inner child without growing your waistline.   

Breakfast

Start your day with an Egg White Delight McMuffin, Fruit ‘N Yogurt Parfait, or Fruit & Maple Oatmeal. Each clocks in with less than 300 calories. Skip the Hash Browns and get a side of Apple Slices instead.

name: Little Caesars Pizza
guide:
Thin is In

Ditch the deep dish and go for the thinner regular or pretzel crust instead - you'll save up to 100 calories.

Veg Out

Pass on the pepperoni and load up your pizza with veggies for an added crunch and nutritional boost!

Skip the Dip

Just 1 container of Caesar's dipping sauces can set you back up to 380 calories. If you want to add a little kick to your slice, add calorie-free red pepper flakes or oregano.

name: Jimmy John's
guide:
Slim Subs

Skip the high calorie Giant Club Sandwiches and go for a Plain Slim instead. Your best bets are the Slim Roast Beef and Slim Turkey Breast which clock in with less than 500 calories each. Ask them to add lettuce and tomato to add an (almost) calorie free crunch. Plain Slims too plain? Try the Big John or Turkey Tom subs for only about 50-100 calories more.

The Unwich

Cut even more calories (and carbs!) by ordering your sub as an Unwich. They'll swap the bread for a lettuce wrap, saving you 280 calories.

Smart Side

Gotta have chips with that sandwich? A bag of Thinny Jimmy Chips will only add 130 calories to your meal.

name: Taco Bell
guide:
Taco Bell allows for customization on most of their menu items so try these suggestions to make your next taco tastier and healthier.

Fresco Menu

Taco Bell offers 7 signature Fresco items that are big on flavor and are only 350 calories (or less!) and under 10 grams of fat. You can also order most items Fresco Style which can reduce the fat in your meal by up to 25%.

More Veggies

Add tomatoes, onions, peppers, lettuce, or salsa to your meal to boost veggie content. Taco Bell also has a wide selection of vegetarian selections to try.

Up the flavor without the calories

Instead of sour cream, cheese, or a creamy sauce, pour on one or more packets of Border Sauce to up the flavor without the guilt. Each packet is 0 calories and there are 4 varieties to try!

Choose Small Drinks

Keep sugary drinks, like soda, small. Save the larger cups for water or unsweetened tea.

guide:

Thin crust, that is! Choose a thin crust instead of hand tossed or pan and save up to calories per medium slice.

Something Different

Avoid fatty meats and go for veggie toppings instead. The more veggies the better, but if you want to include some meat on your next slice avoid high calories options like pepperoni and sausage and choose Canadian bacon or chicken instead.


Stay thin

A thinner crust means fewer calories per slice.


Light Cheese

Order your next pizza with light cheese - less calories but all the flavor!

name: Sonic
guide:
Think small

When it comes to burgers, smaller is better. At Sonic, that means a Jr. Burger or Jr. Deluxe Cheeseburger. Got a hankering for a hot dog? Skip the footlong and stick with a regular New York, All-American, or Chicago Dog.

Go wacky

Keep a lid on calories by ordering a Wacky Pack kid's meal. Pair Chicken Strips, a Jr. Burger, Corn Dog, or Hot Dog with Apple Slices and 1% Milk, Orange Juice, or Apple Juice for a 500-calorie meal. 

Trim chicken

With around 450 calories each, the Classic Grilled Chicken Sandwich and Grilled Chicken Wrap are great choices.

name: Subway
guide:
Subway is a great place for a protein rich meal on the go. If you follow some of these tips you will satisfy your sandwich craving with a big nutritional punch!

Pile on the veggies

Subway lets you add as many veggies as you want at no additional charge! This is a great way to add more nutrients to your sandwich.

Go light on the spreads

Choose light mayo or skip mayo all together and save 50-100 calories. Add some zest with mustard or honey mustard instead.

Choose sweets carefully

Choose apples or a yogurt parfait instead of cookies if you're looking for a sweet ending to your meal.

name: Starbucks
guide:
Caffeine is a morning necessity for millions worldwide. If you’re not a fan of drinking your coffee black or espresso straight, try these suggestions to skim calories, fat, and sugar from your beverage of choice.

Make your latte “skinny”

Lose the whip and substitute nonfat milk  in your latte to cut fat and calories. Lose the sugary syrups and pump up the flavor with the sugar-free versions instead. 

Downsize

If you can't resist that Caramel Macchiato or Vanilla Latte, stick to a modest Tall or Short size to indulge for fewer calories.

Snack smart

For a healthy breakfast on-the-go, try the Whole-Grain Oatmeal, Reduced-Fat Turkey Bacon Breakfast Sandwich, or the Spinach & Feta Breakfast Wrap. Looking for a snack? Satisfy your sweet tooth with seasonal fruit or a Greek yogurt parfait.  If you need something a bit more substantial to battle the afternoon hunger, try the Protein Bistro Box.

name: Panera Bread
guide:
Better Breakfast

Skip the muffins, scones, and pastries and grab a hearty bowl of Steel Cut Oatmeal. Not an oatmeal fan? Try the Strawberry Granola Parfait, Seasonal Fruit Cup, or any of the three Breakfast Power Sandwiches.

Think Thin

Trim the calories from your bagel and schmear with a thin Sprouted Grain Bagel Flat topped with a reduced-fat cream cheese spread. 

Veg Out

With over a dozen salads on the menu, it’s easy to get your veggies at Panera. Most full-size salads clock in with only around 500 calories, so munch on! If it’s gotta be a sandwich, try pairing just half a sandwich with a salad as a You Pick 2 combo.

name: Chick-fil-A
guide:
Go grilled

To keep calories and fat in check, stick with grilled chicken. The Grilled Market Salad, Grilled Chicken Cool Wrap, Grilled Chicken Sandwich, and Grilled Nuggets all clock in with less than 350 calories.

Add fruits and vegetables

Pair your chicken with a Side Salad or Fruit Cup instead of Waffle Fries, Coleslaw, or soup. You'll save calories and get a healthy dose of fruits or veggies.

Be breakfast savvy

Skip the fatty fried chicken, bacon or sausage bagels, biscuits, and burritos and order a Greek Yogurt Parfait or Multigrain Oatmeal instead.

name: IHOP
guide:
Simple & fit

To keep calories in check, order one of the items marked Simple & Fit, like the Simple & Fit Vegetable Omelette or Simple & Fit 2-Egg Breakfast. Each clocks in with less than 400 calories.

Proper pancakes

If it’s gotta be pancakes, keep a lid on sugar and white flour with a short stack (3 pancakes) of the Original Buttermilk Pancakes. Go easy on the syrup - just 2 tablespoons of the Maple Old Fashioned Syrup packs 110 calories. Better yet, try topping your pancakes with the Cinnamon Apple Compote (45 calories) or Sugar Free Syrup (15 calories) instead. 

Lighter lunch and dinner

Not there for breakfast? Try the Citrus Chicken Pecan Salad. It’s 670 calories’ worth of greens, grilled chicken, orange slices, and pecans.

name: Chipotle
guide:
Toss the tortilla

Skip the 320-calorie flour tortilla in that Burrito and opt for a Burrito Bowl instead. You'll save another 200 calories if you lose the rice and swap the Bowl for a Salad. Or strike a balance: ask for a  Bowl with half lettuce and half rice.

Steak is supreme

It may come as a surprise, but the 150-calorie Steak has fewer calories and less saturated fat than any other meat option at Chipotle. Second best? The 180-calorie Chicken. Or skip the meat altogether and go for the 150-calorie tofu Sofritas instead (but be aware: you'll get 1/3 the protein of the meat options). 

Toppings

If you're getting rice, make it brown. Load up on fiber-rich fajita vegetables, beans, and fresh tomato salsa. Go easy on the higher calorie toppings like cheese, sour cream, and guacamole, which add 100-230 calories a pop.

name: Wendy's
guide:
Stick with Jr. size

Getting a burger? Stick with a fewer-than-400-calories Jr. size.  If it's a Frosty you're fantasizing about,  a Jr. size will cost you about 200 calories. That ain't bad.

Choose grilled chicken

For salads, sandwiches, and wraps, choose lean grilled chicken over fried. 

Make a meal out of sides

Pair an order of Rich & Meaty Chili or Baked Potato (hold the cheese) with a Garden Side Salad for a filling meal with around 500 calories.

name: Taco Bell
guide:
Taco Bell allows for customization on most of their menu items so try these suggestions to make your next taco tastier and healthier.

Fresco Menu

Taco Bell offers 7 signature Fresco items that are big on flavor and are only 350 calories (or less!) and under 10 grams of fat. You can also order most items Fresco Style which can reduce the fat in your meal by up to 25%.

More Veggies

Add tomatoes, onions, peppers, lettuce, or salsa to your meal to boost veggie content. Taco Bell also has a wide selection of vegetarian selections to try.

Up the flavor without the calories

Instead of sour cream, cheese, or a creamy sauce, pour on one or more packets of Border Sauce to up the flavor without the guilt. Each packet is 0 calories and there are 4 varieties to try!

Choose Small Drinks

Keep sugary drinks, like soda, small. Save the larger cups for water or unsweetened tea.

name: Little Caesars Pizza
guide:
Thin is In

Ditch the deep dish and go for the thinner regular or pretzel crust instead - you'll save up to 100 calories.

Veg Out

Pass on the pepperoni and load up your pizza with veggies for an added crunch and nutritional boost!

Skip the Dip

Just 1 container of Caesar's dipping sauces can set you back up to 380 calories. If you want to add a little kick to your slice, add calorie-free red pepper flakes or oregano.

name: McDonald's
guide:
Choose Chicken

Lean, grilled chicken is the way to go at McDonald’s. Try it on a veggie-packed salad with a side of low fat dressing or opt for a grilled chicken sandwich or McWrap (hold the sauce) and pump up the produce with a side of Apple Slices or salad.

Stick with Smaller

If it’s gotta be a burger, stick with a slim 250-calorie Hamburger or 300-calorie Cheeseburger.  Try getting one as part of a Happy Meal (yes, adults can eat these too!). With about 500 calories per meal, you’ll treat your inner child without growing your waistline.   

Breakfast

Start your day with an Egg White Delight McMuffin, Fruit ‘N Yogurt Parfait, or Fruit & Maple Oatmeal. Each clocks in with less than 300 calories. Skip the Hash Browns and get a side of Apple Slices instead.

name: Domino's
guide:
Pizza Crust
When it comes to pizza crust, the thinner the better. On average, thin crust pizza at Domino's has 20% fewer calories than hand tossed. Pass on the even thicker pan crust.
Toppings
Pile on those vegetables! Veggies on pizza is a great way to fill up without filling out. If adding protein, stick to the leaner options like chicken or ham and skip the fatty beef, pepperoni, sausage, and steak.
Sides
Pair your pizza with a side salad instead of breadsticks or chicken wings, You'll save calories and add another dose of veggies to your meal.

name: Olive Garden
guide:
Go Easy on the Breadsticks

The breadsticks may be tempting, but at 140 calories a pop they can add up quick. Can’t resist? Ask your server not to bring any to your table. 

Think Green

Boost veggies by starting your meal with a House Salad instead of soup. 

Lighter Italian Fare

Most dinner size entrees and pastas have around 1,000 calories. You can cut calories in half by ordering an entree off the Lighter Italian Fare menu. 

Downsize Dessert

If you can’t leave without dessert, try one of the 200 to 300 calorie Dolcini (mini desserts).

name: Panda Express
guide:
Better bowl

Pick a perfectly portioned Panda Bowl and pair 1 entree with 1 side. Skip the Entree Plates which come with 2 or 3 entrees plus a side.

Wok smart

Look for items marked Wok Smart on the menu and you are guaranteed an entree with 300 calories or less. The lowest of the low? The 150-calorie Broccoli Beef or the 170-calorie Mushroom Chicken

Slim side

Skip the 400 calorie Steamed Rice and the 500 calorie Fried Rice or Chow Mein. Go for the fresh Mixed Vegetables for only 80 calories.

name: Dairy Queen
guide:
Food items

Dairy Queen offers many items that let you trim the calories but not the flavor. Make a healthy meal by choosing the grilled chicken sandwich and pairing it with a side salad with vinaigrette dressing.  You also can't go wrong with the grilled chicken salad which has a satiating 26 grams of protein and only 160 calories. 

Treats

Dairy Queen has many treat options that can fit into a healthy diet. The trick is to keep serving sizes small and limit extra toppings. Choose the small vanilla cone or the small strawberry sundae for only 240 calories each. The fudge bar is also a great option because it has only 50 calories, is fat free and has no added sugar. If the classic DQ Blizzard is more your style, stick with the mini size to limit the impact on your waistline but still make your tastebuds happy.
